  <description>
    <p>The intent of this project is to provide a baseline RTCW which may be used for further development and fun. The map editor and associated compiling tools are not included. We suggest you use a modern copy of GtkRadiant. Some of the major features currently implemented are:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>SDL backend</li>
      <li>OpenAL sound API support (multiple speaker support and better sound quality)</li>
      <li>Full x86_64 support</li>
      <li>AVI video capture of demos</li>
      <li>Much improved console autocompletion &amp; Persistent console history</li>
      <li>Colorized terminal output</li>
      <li>Much improved QVM tools</li>
      <li>Many, many bug fixes</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
     Commercial data files are required to run the supported games. These can be aquired though a multitude of sources. See the manual for more info on this.
    </p>
  </description>

